<Base title="In These Days Of Tumult, Heat And Dazzle I Retreat In My Mind — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>In These Days Of Tumult, Heat And Dazzle I Retreat In My Mind</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">Stefan Gierowski Foundation, Warsaw | 2021</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>Examines contemporary work by young Polish painters, featuring over thirty artists whose paintings reject post-artistic and activist approaches. Rather than adopting critical or ironic stances, the works draw from symbolism, surrealism, expressionism, and decadence. Modern references from gaming, television, and popular culture blend with historical influences in "post-ironic and emotional" ways. Individual paintings create "hybrid, oneiric, dreamlike worlds" exploring mythology, vanitas, ephemerality, magic, and psychedelic themes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Curators:</strong> Michalina Sablik, Kamil Pierwszy</p>
      <p><strong>Artists:</strong> Martyna Borowiecka, Zuzanna Charkiewicz, Krzysztof Gil, Krzysztof Grzybacz, Veronika Hapchenko, Marcin Janusz, Emilia Kina, Karolina Kr&oacute;l, Maja Krysiak, Hanna Krzysztofiak, Marcin &#321;aszczewski, Adam Nehring, Maciej Nowacki, Karolina Nowak, &Oslash;leg&amp;Ka&#347;ka, Katarzyna Olma, Pawe&#322; Olszczy&#324;ski, Pawe&#322; Olszewski, Tomasz Opali&#324;ski, Aleksandra Otulska, Zuzanna Piekoszewska, Martyna Pinkowska, Jan Porczy&#324;ski, Maryna Sakowska, Kuba S&#322;omkowski, Magdalena Starska, &#321;ukasz Stok&#322;osa, Aleksandra Waliszewska, Jan Eustachy Wolski, Joanna Wo&#347;, Katarzyna Wyszkowska, Konrad &#379;u&#322;kowski</p>
      <p><strong>Photography:</strong> Adam Gut</p>
